---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { routes } from '../i18n/routes';

const pressEmail = 'press@aryamind.com';
const fallbackEmail = 'contact@carvetrace.com';
---
<Base
  lang="en"
  pageId="press"
  title="Press kit — CarveTrace / Aryamind SARL"
  description="For journalists, analysts, and industry researchers. Company facts, boilerplate, brand assets, and key dates for the 2026 EU AI Act enforcement window."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Press</p>
    <h1>Press kit</h1>
    <p>
      Everything a journalist, analyst, or industry researcher needs to write
      accurately about CarveTrace and Aryamind SARL. Reuse without prior
      approval ; the site content (excluding logos + branding) is licensed
      CC-BY-4.0. Higher-resolution assets or specific quotes : email
      <a href={`mailto:${pressEmail}`}>{pressEmail}</a> (also
      <a href={`mailto:${fallbackEmail}`}>{fallbackEmail}</a> if you don't
      get a fast reply).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section">
    <h2>Boilerplate (use verbatim)</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>About CarveTrace.</strong> CarveTrace is the only EU AI Act
      evidence layer whose verdict is re-verifiable by a third party
      without trusting the vendor. Every AI decision and the human-oversight
      event that reviewed it are bound at write-time as a single signed
      atom. The verifier is open-source (Apache 2.0) and runs in any
      modern browser — at <a href="https://verify.carvetrace.com">verify.carvetrace.com</a>
      — with no account required. The producer-side SDKs are self-hosted
      across every tier ; Aryamind never touches customer data.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>About Aryamind SARL.</strong> Aryamind is a French SARL based
      in France, founded in 2025. CarveTrace is its product line. Aryamind
      is privately funded, EU-domiciled, and serves customers across EU and
      EEA enterprises with AI Act Article 12 + 14 compliance obligations
      under the 2 August 2026 high-risk deadline and the 9 December 2026
      Product Liability Directive applicability.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section">
    <h2>Key facts</h2>
    <table class="press-table">
      <tbody>
        <tr><th>Company</th><td>Aryamind SARL</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Product</th><td>CarveTrace (v0.4 in production as of June 2026)</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Country of incorporation</th><td>France</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Founded</th><td>2025</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Funding</th><td>Privately funded</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Headcount</th><td>Founder-only as of June 2026</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Customer footprint</th><td>EU and EEA enterprises with AI Act high-risk AI systems ; in design-partner phase ahead of August 2026 enforcement</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Open-source</th><td>Verifier libraries + protocol definitions are Apache 2.0 ; producer-side SDKs are proprietary commercial</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Pricing</th><td>Verifier free / Starter €15K/yr / Growth €45K/yr / Enterprise from €90K, per high-risk AI system × decision volume (<a href={routes.pricing.en}>full pricing</a>)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section">
    <h2>What makes the product newsworthy</h2>
    <ul class="press-list">
      <li><strong>Cryptographic re-verifiability.</strong> No other AI Governance Platform (CredoAI, OneTrust, IBM watsonx.governance, Holistic AI, ModelOp, Saidot, Monitaur, TrueScreen, etc.) ships a verifier that an auditor's auditor can run in their browser without trusting the vendor. CarveTrace does ; the verifier is open-source.</li>
      <li><strong>Article 12 ↔ Article 14 binding at write-time.</strong> Every AI inference is cryptographically bound to the human-oversight event that reviewed it as a single signed atom. Monitaur logs decisions ; TrueScreen certifies data with eIDAS qualified timestamps. Neither binds inference ↔ oversight as one atom.</li>
      <li><strong>EU-domiciled + self-hosted.</strong> Aryamind SARL is a French company. CarveTrace is self-hosted on the customer's infrastructure across every tier. No US-vendor transfer-impact issues ; no shared SaaS plane ; customer's signing keys never leave customer custody.</li>
      <li><strong>Honest pricing.</strong> Prices on the page : €0 / €15K / €45K / from €90K. Per high-risk AI system × decision volume — the unit the EU AI Act regulates. No "contact sales" wall ; no per-seat trap.</li>
      <li><strong>Designed for the PLD.</strong> The Product Liability Directive 2024/2853 applies to AI from 9 December 2026. The Directive shifts the burden of disclosure to the producer. An evidence layer that can't be verified by a claimant's expert independently is one that doesn't survive contested litigation. CarveTrace was built for this.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section">
    <h2>Founder bio</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Othman Chahboune</strong> — Founder, Aryamind SARL. Engineer
      and operator based in France. Previously built cryptographic data
      systems at scale ; founded Aryamind in 2025 to bring third-party-
      re-verifiable evidence to AI compliance. CarveTrace's commitment to
      ship a verifier that survives the vendor is a direct reaction to a
      pattern of vendor-database-locked compliance products that have
      historically failed customers when the vendor was acquired,
      went out of business, or rotated keys.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section">
    <h2>Logos + brand assets</h2>
    <p>
      The CarveTrace wordmark and monogram are trademarks of Aryamind SARL.
      Use them only to identify or reference CarveTrace itself — not to
      imply endorsement of your own product, service, or content. Permitted
      uses do not require prior written authorization. For media coverage,
      below are direct links to the assets shipped on this site :
    </p>
    <ul class="press-list">
      <li><a href="/favicon.svg" rel="noopener">Monogram (SVG, 1× scalable)</a> — the C-shaped favicon ; sized for browser-tab use, also works at button-icon scale.</li>
      <li>Wordmark : <em>Carve</em><strong>Trace</strong> rendered in Inter SemiBold + Inter Regular at any size. No bitmap version is shipped because the wordmark is text — render it in your typesetter at any DPI.</li>
      <li>Brand palette : emerald primary <code>#15803d</code> + zinc neutral <code>#18181b</code> + ink-secondary <code>#52525b</code> + edge <code>#e4e4e7</code>. Background white.</li>
      <li>Type : Inter (sans, body + headings) + JetBrains Mono (monospace, hash chips + code blocks).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Need a higher-resolution wordmark export (PNG / PDF) ? Email
      <a href={`mailto:${pressEmail}`}>{pressEmail}</a> with the use case
      and target resolution. Turnaround : 1 business day.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section">
    <h2>Sample screenshots</h2>
    <p>
      Permitted for editorial use with attribution to "CarveTrace" or
      "verify.carvetrace.com" where relevant :
    </p>
    <ul class="press-list">
      <li><strong>Verifier landing page.</strong> Open <a href="https://verify.carvetrace.com">verify.carvetrace.com</a> in any modern browser ; full-page screenshot is the canonical asset.</li>
      <li><strong>Verifier VERIFIED state.</strong> Drop the <a href="https://verify.carvetrace.com/sample-evidence-bundle.zip">valid sample bundle</a> onto the verifier, screenshot the VERIFIED card.</li>
      <li><strong>Verifier FAILED state.</strong> Drop the <a href="https://verify.carvetrace.com/sample-evidence-bundle-tampered.zip">tampered sample bundle</a> ; screenshot the FAILED card.</li>
      <li><strong>Coverage report dossier excerpt.</strong> Generate a report bundle per the <a href="/demo/">demo</a> guide ; screenshot the cand-delta override dossier (the AI Act recruitment-scenario story).</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section">
    <h2>Key dates referenced in CarveTrace coverage</h2>
    <table class="press-table">
      <tbody>
        <tr><th>2 August 2026</th><td>EU AI Act high-risk obligations bind (Article 12 + Article 14)</td></tr>
        <tr><th>9 December 2026</th><td>Product Liability Directive 2024/2853 applies to AI software</td></tr>
        <tr><th>2 August 2027</th><td>EU AI Act full applicability (including embedded-in-regulated-product systems)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section">
    <h2>Useful links for further research</h2>
    <ul class="press-list">
      <li><a href={routes.why.en}>/why</a> — comparison of CarveTrace vs CredoAI / OneTrust / IBM watsonx.governance / Holistic AI / ModelOp / Saidot / TrueScreen / build-it-yourself, on 8 dimensions.</li>
      <li><a href={routes.docs.en}>/docs</a> — 30+ technical and regulatory guides, versioned with the code.</li>
      <li><a href={routes.blog.en}>/blog</a> — long-read analyses of Article 12, Article 14, and the PLD's burden-shift mechanic.</li>
      <li><a href={routes.trust.en}>/trust</a> — security posture, certifications roadmap, vendor-questionnaire pre-answers.</li>
      <li><a href="/verifier-integrity/">/verifier-integrity</a> — published SHA-256 manifest of every asset on verify.carvetrace.com ; auditors can rebuild from source and compare.</li>
      <li><a href={routes.deck.en}>/deck</a> — 10-slide pitch deck for context on the product narrative.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="press-section press-contact">
    <h2>Press contact</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Email :</strong> <a href={`mailto:${pressEmail}`}>{pressEmail}</a> (also <a href={`mailto:${fallbackEmail}`}>{fallbackEmail}</a> as fallback).
      <br/>
      <strong>Response window :</strong> 1 business day during EU business hours (CET, Mon–Fri 09:00–18:00).
      <br/>
      <strong>Interview language :</strong> EN or FR.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .press-section { margin: 2.5rem 0; max-width: 56rem; }
  .press-section h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .press-section > p {
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .press-section code {
    background: #f4f4f5;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }

  .press-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .press-table th, .press-table td {
    border: 1px solid var(--edge-subtle);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .press-table th {
    background: #f4f4f5;
    font-weight: 600;
    width: 32%;
  }

  .press-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .press-list li {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .press-list li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55rem;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: var(--brand-600);
    opacity: 0.85;
  }
  .press-list strong { color: var(--ink-default); }
  .press-list a { color: var(--brand-600); text-decoration: underline; }

  .press-section p strong { color: var(--ink-default); }
  .press-section p a { color: var(--brand-600); text-decoration: underline; }

  .press-contact {
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    background: #fafafa;
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
  }
  .press-contact p { margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.7; }
</style>
